article.headline: Presbyterian 42, Davidson 6
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- Myron Gary threw for a career-high, Trandon Dendy ran for a career-high and Presbyterian recorded one of the most lopsided victories in its Division I history Saturday with a 42-6 rout of Davidson. Gary passed for a career-high 153 yards and two touchdowns and Dendy also scored two touchdowns, rushing for a career-high 162 yards on 18 carries. The 42 points is the most the Blue Hose (2-9) have scored since a 45-21 victory over VMI on Oct. 13, 2007. The six points was the fewest allowed in their Division I history. Michael Ruff caught two touchdowns for Presbyterian. Jonathan Carkhuff completed 17 of 29 passes and an interception for Davidson (3-8). His 144 yards passing Saturday gave him 2,002 for the season. Kenny Mantuo ran for Davidson's lone touchdown.
